\right)^{-1}$, where $\\sigma_{\\min}(A)$\nis the minimum singular value of the matrix $A$. The matrix $C_{2n}$ is a\nrandom circulant matrix and $S_n:=F^*_{2,n} D_{1,n}^{-1}F_{2,n} + F^*_{4,n}\nD^{-1}_2 F_{4,n}$, where $F_{2,n},F_{4,n}$ are deterministic matrices and\n$D_{1,n}, D_{2,n}$ are random diagonal matrices. We conjeture $S_n$ is well\nconditioned.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 19 May 2020 22:18:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 28 Sep 2020 22:12:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-30"}
