end-to-end perspective. We detail their capabilities and functionalities\nfocusing on how their constituting elements fit the 5G ecosystem, and unravel\nthe interactions among the surveyed solutions. Finally, we review hardware and\ntestbeds on which these frameworks can run, and discuss the limitations of the\nstate-of-the-art, as well as feasible directions toward fully open source,\nprogrammable 5G networks.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 May 2020 13:18:29 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 21 May 2020 17:01:51 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 25 Aug 2020 20:40:01 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sun, 6 Sep 2020 15:36:51 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Wed, 10 Feb 2021 19:16:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-12"}
